Roots do NOT work.  When I hit lvl 16 I could not root a snake.  I got Enstill, which is either resisted or does NOT stick on 90% of mobs cast upon.  Bonds of Force... everyone told me I would love this spell... I DON'T.  It is resisted by gnolls in Qeynos!  I'm not talking about fizzles here, I am talking about flat out NOT WORKING!  When I notified a GM I was informed that the root line of spells had been nerfed for Wizards to &quot;balance&quot; the classes.  If a mage can have his pet root a mob and have it stick, why cant I do the same?  <br>
<br>
I cannot solo because I cannot root and cast.  Everyone says kite.  Fine idea if the spells sticks, certain death if it doesnt and you dont know if it's going to stick when you cast it.  The GMs have told me that VI is more interested in grouping and learning to work together than the solo Wizzie running around getting XP.  That's pure BS.  If a mage can solo why can't I?  That's truly the question.  If a warrior can solo, why not a wizzie?<br>
<br>
Fizzles are not bad if you truly practice and cast all types of spells.  I suck at divination, but Evocation and Abjuration are through the roof because Im always shielding myself then nuking something.  I put in practice points where I can.  Being a high elf I do not cast the sight spells since I see well enough, thank you very much.  So I'm penalized for my race.  (I'm not going to get started on my theory that VI only wants high level Erudite Wizards)<br>
<br>
I usually only fizzle at the beginning a new level and then those are few and far between.  Give me something that will work... PLEASE!</font><P>Severine <BR>
